Most recently, Standard & Poor downgraded SA even deeper into junk status. On the upside, as a result of the country's coronavirus response led by President Cyril Ramaphosa, S&P upgraded SA's outlook from negative to stable. But does that really provide a silver lining and give our country — and international investors — something positive to hang their hats on? Peter Bruce, former editor-in-chief of Business Day and Financial Mail, speaks to the leaders of some of SA’s most prominent banking and financial services institutions about their expectations of life in a post-lockdown SA. Bruce is joined by: This timely Business Day Dialogue provides insights from those leading the charge towards economic recovery, and the realities we should expect as we move forward.